---
import { loadEnv } from "../env";
const env = loadEnv();
const tallyUrl = `https://tally.so/r/${env.TALLY_FORM_ID}`;
---
<section class="hero" aria-labelledby="hero-headline">
  <h1 id="hero-headline">Stop reinventing a backend every time your agent builds you one.</h1>
  <p class="hero-lede">
    Your first Cursor-built approval tool shipped in two days. The fourth one has a schema
    you've never seen, events that half-work, and a review queue nobody reads.
  </p>
  <p class="hero-pitch">
    rntme is a standard runtime for these services. One blueprint describes the domain,
    the data, the state, the API, and the UI. The runtime enforces it.
    Service&nbsp;#10 looks like service&nbsp;#1.
  </p>
  <div class="hero-ctas">
    <a class="btn btn-primary" href={tallyUrl}>Apply as a pilot team →</a>
    <a class="btn btn-secondary" href={env.GITHUB_URL}>GitHub</a>
  </div>
  <p class="hero-proof">
    Safe by construction · Validated blueprints · Zero service-specific code · Works with your agents
  </p>
</section>

<style>
  .hero { padding: var(--space-6) var(--space-4); }
  .hero h1 { font-size: var(--fs-display); line-height: var(--lh-tight); margin: 0 0 var(--space-4); }
  .hero-lede, .hero-pitch { font-size: var(--fs-body); max-width: 62ch; margin: 0 0 var(--space-3); }
  .hero-ctas { display: flex; gap: var(--space-3); margin: var(--space-5) 0 var(--space-4); flex-wrap: wrap; }
  .hero-proof { color: var(--color-text-muted); font-size: var(--fs-small); }
</style>
